<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,697,793]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,200,697,721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Notes</emphasis>
:—The fossil-species 
<taxonomicName authority="Massalongo (1858)" authorityName="Massalongo" authorityYear="1858" box="[437,831,697,721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myricoides">
<emphasis box="[437,603,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ilex myricoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Massalongo, A. B." box="[612,831,697,721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" refId="ref2972" refString="Massalongo, A. B. (1858) Synopsis florae fossilis senogalliensis. apud A. Merlo, Verona [Veronae], 136 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 7733" type="book" year="1858">Massalongo (1858)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was based on the fossil leaves from the Upper Miocene (Messinian) of 
<collectingCountry box="[295,346,733,757]" name="Italy" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Italy</collectingCountry>
. However, it is a later homonym of the extant 
<taxonomicName authority="Kunth (1824)" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1824" box="[819,1131,733,757]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myricoides">
<emphasis box="[819,981,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ilex myricoides</emphasis>
Kunth (1824)
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, a new replacement name is validated for the fossil-species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
